    public class GameCell
extends javafx.scene.canvas.Canvas
implements java.io.Serializable
    This class is the basis for all game play. These hold in-game information and display graphics.

    • Constructor Detail

      • GameCell

        public GameCell(java.lang.String cellType,
                int row,
                int col,
                boolean captured,
                boolean scouted,
                boolean neutral,
                boolean hostile,
                boolean destroyed,
                int soldiers,
                int materials,
                int cores,
                int enemies,
                boolean capturable,
                boolean scoutable,
                boolean destroyable)
        Creates a new GameCell object using the given cell type, row, and column; This should be the main constructor used (especially when generating maps);
        Parameters:
        cellType - the type of game cell
        row - the cell's row in a grid layout
        col - the cell's column in a grid layout
        captured - whether or not the GameCell is initially captured
        scouted - whether or not the GameCell is initially scouted
        neutral - whether or not the GameCell is initially neutral
        hostile - whether or not the GameCell is initially hostile
        destroyed - whether or not the GameCell is initially destroyed
        soldiers - the number of soldiers that the cell initially contains
        materials - the number of building materials that the cell initially contains
        cores - the number of energy cores that the cell initially contains
        enemies - the number of enemies that the cell initially contains
        capturable - whether or not this cell is capturable
        scoutable - whether or not this cell is scoutable
        destroyable - whether or not this cell is destroyable

        Sets the enemies field to the passed in value;
        Parameters:
